  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "@Haroenv Why would it be for debugging?\r\n\r\nThe whole point is to not duplicate the logic that we have about \"current index\" (remember that this logic changed when we introduced Federated Search). In the next big refactor, we won't have to think about this logic a different places, it's all contained in `getWidgetRenderState`.\r\n\r\nNow we don't need to worry how to get the \"current index\" value because we use the API that we expose to users to retrieve this value, _and this is exactly what Render State is about_.\r\n\r\nAnd if you're concerned about the function being called at the top of the function, you shouldn't. The whole point of `getWidgetRenderState` is that it can be called whenever because it doesn't trigger side effects.",
    "created_at": "2020-11-05T09:14:17Z",
    "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/pull/4571#issuecomment-722248376",
    "id": 722248376,
