  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "It lowers room for inconsistency, which is what we aim for in this codebase.\r\n\r\nI'm wondering if you're surprised because you're used to seeing this lifecycle function called only this way?\r\n\r\n```ts\r\nrenderFn(\r\n  {\r\n    ...this.getWidgetRenderState(initOptions),\r\n    instantSearchInstance,\r\n  },\r\n  true\r\n);\r\n```\r\n\r\nIt shouldn't be the only way we call it. It's a bit like if you would ban using `props` in a React component somewhere else than in its rendering `return` expression.\r\n\r\nYou could also see it that way:\r\n\r\n`props` → `getProps` (because we don't have the reactive system of React) → `getWidgetRenderState` (rename to our concept)",
    "created_at": "2020-11-05T16:51:27Z",
    "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/pull/4571#issuecomment-722501085",
